description.narrative:
Award covers three outputs to support:
Reintegration of returnees;
Self-reliance of RAE;
Law on Language Use.

comment.narrative:
Analytical study on Human Resource Development in Tourism and Hospitality designed;  
Report on strengthening dialogue and cooperation between central and local institution in relation to the economic development drafted for DoI with clear action plan for its implementation;
Sector profiles of Plastic and Rubber industry and Chemicals industry developed.

-Ministry of Justice  effectively coordinates between national institutions in the rule of law sector.
- 25% of Kosovo judges and 30%  of Kosovo prosecutors trained on the application of human rights stands and norms (including on the application of provisions of the Law on Protection from Discrimination);
- Law on Mediation Drafted;
--Guidelines for harmonizing judicial practices (criminal and civil field) at the Basic Courts and Court of Appeal are finalized and published/ Bulletin no 2 published and distributed.

•	Technical and Advisory Support to Minister’s Cabinet, Secretary General’s Office, Department for the Management of Public Administration Reform, the Department for Civil Service Administration, Department for Registration and Liaison with NGOs, and the Kosovo Institute for Public Administration (KIPA);
•	200 civil servants from the central and municipal level trained on Common Assessment Framework (CAF);
•	250 Human Resource Officials trained on Information Management System in Civil Service (HRIMS) for more than 250 Human Resource Officials;
•	More than 4500 NGOs application folders registered and classified in the electronic system; 
•	The establishment of the Monitoring System for the Implementation of Principles of Ethics and Integrity on Civil Service, as well as the development of the Integrity Plan for MPA;
•	Feasibility Study on Establishment of a Credit System for KIPA Trainings;
•	Regulation for Trainings of Civil Servants;
•	Legal Document on defining the mechanisms to measure the quality and accessibility of public services to citizens;
•	Mystery Shopping survey on measuring public perception concerning the quality and accountability of public services;
•	The development of an electronic-box provides citizens with the possibility to freely express their opinions on administrative services provided at the central and local level either at the place where the services are provided or through an e-Portal.

•	The development of an electronic system (Citizens’ Satisfactory Information System/CSIS) on measuring citizens’ perception on the service delivery. 
•	Public Awareness Campaign on the use of the CSIS; Visualization Platform for data deriving from CSIS; 
•	100 HR Managers were trained on the implementation and functionality of the Monitoring System in the civil service, with focus on the HR functions; 
•	Job classification and standardization of job processes for 10,521 civil servants from 33 municipalities, 18 ministries, and 36 agencies, which were harmonized and adjusted to the Human Resource Information Management System (HRIMS) and will serve as a platform for all civil service; 
•	5,500 folders with NGO documents were reviewed, classified, identified with a serial number and filled in the newly-established electronic system; 
•	Concept Document on determining the approaches for institutionalization of the integrity planning in all Kosovo institutions;
•	Drafting of the Regulation on Management of e-governance project, as well as the Regulation on Administrations of the Databases; 
•	Concept Document on the Non-Contractual Responsibility of the Public Administration Bodies drafted;
